Qualcomm has introduced its new Snapdragon 710 mobile platform, which promises in-demand premium features for mid-range smartphones. The Snapdragon 710 is built on 10nm process technology, and is designed with efficient architectures for artificial intelligence – featuring a multi-core AI Engine and neural network processing capabilities. The Snapdragon 710 is the first platform in Qualcomm’s new 700-tier, offering technologies and features previously only available in its premium-tier (800) mobile platforms. The Snapdragon 710 provides significant performance improvements over the 600-tier in AI, photography, display, connectivity, and battery performance. The Snapdragon 710 is available immediately and is expected to be found in consumer devices in the second quarter of 2018. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>